<div><p><p>Describe the concept of sampling distribution of mean with reference to the population data (20, 21, 22 & 23) of size 4. In order to explain this, perform simple random sampling with replacement taking all possible samples with sample size n = 2. While describing the sampling distribution following issues will be covered.</p>
<ol>
<li>population mean & population variance, and its distribution</li>
<li>Sample mean & sample variance, and its distribution</li>
<li>Comparison of population mean and sample mean; population variance and sample variance; population distribution and sampling distribution based on the given data.</li>
<li>Standard error of mean</li>
<li>Final comments based on your result</li>
</ol</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18935" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1-1.jpg" alt="" width="569" height="611"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18937" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2-1.jpg" alt="" width="419" height="553"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18941" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3-1.jpg" alt="" width="583" height="501"></p>
