<p>Σy = 28, Σx<sub>1</sub> = 27, Σx<sub>2</sub> = 32, Σyx<sub>1</sub> = 77, Σyx<sub>2</sub> = 154, Σx<sub>1</sub>x<sub>2</sub> = 91, Σy<sup>2</sup> = 140, Σx<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> = 143, Σx<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup> = 182</p>
<p>n= 7</p>
<p>Let the regression equation of y on x<sub>1</sub>, x<sub>2</sub> be</p>
<p>y = b<sub>0</sub> + b<sub>1</sub>x<sub>1</sub> + b<sub>2</sub>x<sub>2</sub>   &#8212;&#8212; (i)</p>
<p>where b<sub>0</sub>, b<sub>1</sub>, b<sub>2</sub> are regression coefficients.</p>
<p>By least square method, The normal equations to the above equations are</p>
<p>Σy = nb<sub>0</sub> + b<sub>1</sub>Σx<sub>1</sub> + b<sub>2</sub>Σx<sub>2</sub></p>
<p>28 = 7b<sub>0</sub> + 27b<sub>1</sub> + 32b<sub>2</sub>        &#8212;&#8212;&#8211;(ii)</p>
<p>Σyx<sub>1</sub> = b<sub>0</sub>Σx<sub>1</sub> + b<sub>1</sub>Σx<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> + b<sub>2</sub>Σx<sub>1</sub>Σx<sub>2</sub></p>
<p>77 = 27b<sub>0</sub> + 143b<sub>1</sub> + 91b<sub>2</sub>               &#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8211;(iii)</p>
<p>Σyx<sub>2</sub> = b<sub>0</sub>Σx<sub>2</sub> + b<sub>2</sub>Σx<sub>1</sub>Σx<sub>2</sub> + b<sub>2</sub>Σx<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup></p>
<p>154 = 32b<sub>0</sub> + 91b<sub>1</sub> + 182b<sub>2            &#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;-(iv)</sub></p>
<p>Solving the equation (ii) , (iii) and (iv) we get the value of regression coefficient.</p>
<p>b<sub>0</sub> = 6.96, b<sub>1</sub> = -0.79 and b<sub>2</sub> = 0.015</p>
<p>Therefore, The final regression model is:-</p>
<p>ŷ = 6.96 + (-0.79)b<sub>1</sub> + 0.015b<sub>2</sub></p>
<p>Here, b<sub>0</sub> = 6.96 is the lifetime when playtime and RAM are considered to be zero.</p>
<p>b<sub>1</sub> = -0.79 means the lifetime decrease by 0.79 per unit change in playtime keeping RAM constant.</p>
<p>b<sub>2</sub> = 0.015 means the lifetime increase by 0.015 per unit change in RAM keeping playtime constant.</p>
